<!doctype html>
<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><title>H38-T003 Shop Flow Review</title><style>@page{margin:.6in}body{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:11pt;line-height:1.45;color:#111827;max-width:8.1in;margin:0 auto;background:#fff}h1{background:#1f2937;color:#fff;padding:16px 18px;border-radius:10px;font-size:22pt;margin:0 0 14px}h2{color:#0f172a;border-bottom:2px solid #cbd5e1;padding-bottom:4px;margin:18px 0 8px;font-size:15pt}p{margin:8px 0 12px}ul,ol{margin:8px 0 14px 24px}li{margin:4px 0}table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;table-layout:fixed;margin:10px 0 16px}th,td{border:1px solid #b7c3d0;padding:8px 9px;vertical-align:top;word-wrap:break-word}th{background:#dbeafe;color:#0f172a;text-align:left}.meta{background:#f8fafc;border:1px solid #dbe3ec;border-radius:10px;padding:10px 12px}.visual{text-align:center;margin:12px 0 16px}.visual img{width:100%;max-width:7.15in;height:auto;border:1px solid #cbd5e1;border-radius:10px}.note{background:#f0fdf4;border-left:6px solid #22c55e;padding:10px 12px;margin:12px 0 16px;border-radius:6px}</style></head><body><h1>Highway 38 Solutions - Shop Flow Review</h1><p class="meta"><b>Sample ID:</b> H38-T003<br><b>Scenario:</b> Repair bay clutter to cleaner workflow</p><div class="visual"><img src="../assets/sample-shop-flow-proof.svg" alt="Shop flow visual"></div><h2>Customer input</h2><ul><li>Five shop photos and one rough hand sketch.</li><li>Repeated jobs: oil changes, brake jobs, small repair work, parts storage.</li><li>Main problem: tools, parts, and vehicles fight for the same lane.</li></ul><h2>Flow zones</h2><table><colgroup><col style="width:25%"><col style="width:38%"><col style="width:37%"></colgroup><tr><th>Zone</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Rule</th></tr><tr><td>Work bay</td><td>Active vehicle work.</td><td>No storage pile inside active lane.</td></tr><tr><td>Daily tool zone</td><td>Common tools.</td><td>Keep within reach of bay.</td></tr><tr><td>Parts staging</td><td>Parts for active jobs.</td><td>One bin or shelf per job.</td></tr><tr><td>Overflow</td><td>Low-use items.</td><td>Move out of the work bay.</td></tr></table><h2>First five fixes</h2><ol><li>Clear the active bay lane.</li><li>Move daily tools closest to bay.</li><li>Create one active-job parts shelf.</li><li>Separate dirty work and clean storage.</li><li>Move low-use items out of the bay.</li></ol><div class="note"><b>Customer-ready summary:</b> You do not need a full shop remodel first. You need a clean lane, daily-use tool zone, and repeatable parts staging rule.</div></body></html>